/**
 * SF Bay Ferry Routes + Shipping Lanes — Safety Overlay
 *
 * All geometry is routed to stay on navigable water. Coordinates
 * pass scripts/validate-ferry-routes.ts against the OSM coastline
 * polygons in data/geo/sf-bay-coastline.json. They were either
 * copied from validated verified-routes.ts paths or generated by
 * scripts/fix-ferry-routes.ts, which inserts perpendicular
 * waypoints until every segment stays in water.
 *
 * Validation:
 *   npx tsx scripts/validate-ferry-routes.ts
 *   npx tsx scripts/fix-ferry-routes.ts       # regenerates /tmp/ferry-routes-fixed.json
 *
 * Sources:
 *   - Golden Gate Ferry (Sausalito / Larkspur schedules + track maps)
 *   - SF Bay Ferry / WETA (Oakland / Alameda / Richmond / Vallejo)
 *   - Blue & Gold Fleet (Tiburon / Angel Island)
 *   - Alcatraz City Cruises
 *   - NOAA Chart 18649 + USCG COTP San Francisco Bay TSS
 *
 * Coordinates are [lng, lat] (GeoJSON order). Ferries travel 20-34 kts
 * and cannot stop quickly — kayaks and SUPs are nearly invisible to
 * ferry crews, especially in fog. The overlay is advisory, not a
 * real-time AIS feed.
 */

